  "cells": [
    {
      "id": "6bdd295e",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Binary Trees: Terminology & Traversals — Practice\n\n**Instructions:** for each Part, **fill in and run every exercise block first**, then run the **checker cell** at the end of that Part to grade all of them at once. Don't run the checker cell partway through — any exercise you haven't filled in yet will simply be marked wrong, since it still holds its empty default value.\n\n**Format:** every question gives you a place to type a plaintext answer (a word, short phrase, or a comma-separated sequence) directly into a `String` variable. **Running an exercise cell only saves your answer — it does not grade it.** Grading happens in the separate checker cell further down (one checker per Part, covering several exercises at once). You can edit your answers and re-run both the exercise cells and the checker cell as many times as you like.\n\n**Time budget:** roughly 60 minutes total.\n- Part 1 — Terminology (~15 min)\n- Part 2 — Traversal definitions (~10 min)\n- Part 3 — Hand-tracing traversals on given trees (~35 min)\n\nRun the setup cell below first — it only needs to run once.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "6bdd295e"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a118f65e",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.*;\n\n// Checks a single short-answer term against a list of acceptable answers.\n// Comparison is case-insensitive and ignores leading/trailing whitespace.\npublic boolean checkTerm(String given, String... accepted) {\n    String norm = given.trim().toLowerCase();\n    for (String a : accepted) {\n        if (norm.equals(a.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n            System.out.println(\"Correct!\");\n            return true;\n        }\n    }\n    System.out.println(\"Not quite. You answered: \\\"\" + given + \"\\\"\");\n    return false;\n}\n\n// Checks a traversal sequence like \"X, Q, M, T, R, Z, J\" against the correct sequence.\n// Accepts variation in spacing/commas and is case-insensitive.\npublic boolean checkSequence(String given, String correctCsv) {\n    String[] givenParts = given.trim().toLowerCase().split(\"[,\\\\s]+\");\n    String[] correctParts = correctCsv.trim().toLowerCase().split(\"[,\\\\s]+\");\n    boolean ok = Arrays.equals(givenParts, correctParts);\n    if (ok) {\n        System.out.println(\"Correct! Sequence: \" + String.join(\", \", correctParts));\n    } else {\n        System.out.println(\"Not quite.\");\n        System.out.println(\"  You answered:  \" + String.join(\", \", givenParts));\n        System.out.println(\"  Correct order: \" + String.join(\", \", correctParts));\n    }\n    return ok;\n}\n\nSystem.out.println(\"Checker functions loaded.\");",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "01463688",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "---\n## Part 1 — Terminology (~15 min)\n\nShort answers only — a single word or short phrase. Don't overthink the wording; the checker accepts common variants.\n\n**Fill in all of 1a–1q below, then run the single checker cell at the end of Part 1.**",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "01463688"
      }
    },
    {
