    {
      "id": "fb6b6eac",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "int part1Score = 0;\n\nif (checkTerm(answer1a, \"tree\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1b, \"root\", \"root node\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1c, \"depth\", \"level\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1d, \"children\", \"child\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1e, \"parent\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1f, \"sibling\", \"siblings\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1g, \"descendant\", \"descendants\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1h, \"ancestor\", \"ancestors\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1i, \"leaf\", \"leaf node\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1j, \"interior\", \"interior node\", \"non-leaf node\", \"non-leaf\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1k, \"subtree\", \"a subtree\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1l, \"path\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1m, \"length\", \"length of a path\", \"path length\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1n, \"height\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1o, \"graph\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1p, \"n-ary\", \"n-ary tree\", \"nary tree\", \"nary\")) part1Score++;\nif (checkTerm(answer1q, \"binary tree\", \"binary\")) part1Score++;\n\nSystem.out.println();\nSystem.out.println(\"Part 1 score: \" + part1Score + \" / 17\");",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "bc4d3562",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "---\n## Part 2 — Traversal Definitions (~10 min)\n\nFor each traversal, describe the **order** in which root, left subtree, and right subtree are visited. Type your answer as three words separated by commas, e.g. `left, root, right`. Just use the plain words \"left\", \"root\", \"right\" — no need for full sentences like \"visit the left subtree first.\" The order you list them in is what's graded.\n\n**Fill in 2a–2c below, then run the checker cell at the end of Part 2.**",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "bc4d3562"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "7879525b",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Exercise 2a\n\nPreorder traversal visits the root, left subtree, and right subtree in what order?",
