    {
      "id": "6b41f3b6",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "---\n## Part 3 — Hand-Tracing Traversals (~35 min)\n\nFor each tree below, work out each traversal **by hand** (no code, no running anything except the checker) and type the sequence of node labels as a comma-separated list, e.g. `X, Q, M, T, R, Z, J`. Spacing doesn't matter and the checker is case-insensitive.\n\nIn addition to preorder/inorder/postorder, each tree also asks for a **level-order** traversal: visit nodes level by level (the \"Level 1, Level 2, ...\" levels from Part 1's terminology), and within each level, visit left to right.\n\n**Each tree's diagram is repeated above every question so you don't have to scroll back and forth. Fill in all of a tree's exercises first, then run that tree's checker cell.**",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "6b41f3b6"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "5f78ca1d",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Tree 1\n\n```\n         X\n        / \\\n       Q   Z\n      / \\   \\\n     M   T   J\n        /\n       R\n```\n\n**3a.** Give the **preorder** traversal of Tree 1.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "5f78ca1d"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "0f4b368f",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "String answer3a = \"\";\nSystem.out.println(\"(answer saved \\u2014 run the checker cell below for grading)\");",
      "metadata": {
