    {
      "id": "05779e93",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Check Tree 1 answers",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "05779e93"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "24d6e636",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "int tree1Score = 0;\nif (checkSequence(answer3a, \"X, Q, M, T, R, Z, J\")) tree1Score++;\nif (checkSequence(answer3b, \"M, Q, R, T, X, Z, J\")) tree1Score++;\nif (checkSequence(answer3c, \"M, R, T, Q, J, Z, X\")) tree1Score++;\nif (checkSequence(answer3d, \"X, Q, Z, M, T, J, R\")) tree1Score++;\nSystem.out.println();\nSystem.out.println(\"Tree 1 score: \" + tree1Score + \" / 4\");",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "id": "d51e1a0c",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "### Tree 2\n\n```\n            M\n          /   \\\n         H     T\n        / \\     \\\n       E   K     W\n        \\       /\n         F     S\n```\n\nNote the empty branches: `H` has both children, but `E` only has a right child (`F`), `T` only has a right child (`W`), and `W` only has a left child (`S`). Be careful — these \"gaps\" are exactly where it's easy to make a mistake.\n\n**3e.** Give the **preorder** traversal of Tree 2.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "d51e1a0c"
      }
    },
    {
