      "source": "### Tree 2\n\n```\n            M\n          /   \\\n         H     T\n        / \\     \\\n       E   K     W\n        \\       /\n         F     S\n```\n\nNote the empty branches: `H` has both children, but `E` only has a right child (`F`), `T` only has a right child (`W`), and `W` only has a left child (`S`). Be careful — these \"gaps\" are exactly where it's easy to make a mistake.\n\n**3f.** Give the **inorder** traversal of Tree 2.",
